President Donald J. Trump will welcome President Rebelo de Sousa of Portugal to the White House on June 27, 2018. The visit will highlight the strong relationship between the United States and Portugal, as well as the importance of the Portuguese-American community. Portugal is a valuable NATO ally and has been involved in partnership efforts with the United States in Afghanistan, crisis regions in Africa, and pressuring North Korea. The leaders will discuss deepening cooperation in addressing global conflicts, promoting economic prosperity, and strengthening energy security. They will engage in a private conversation followed by an expanded bilateral meeting.